# Chakra UI Styling Rules

## Component Imports

Always import from `@chakra-ui/react`:

```typescript
import {
  Box, Flex, VStack, HStack,
  Text, Heading,
  Button, Input, Textarea,
  Card, Table, Badge, Dialog,
  Field, Alert, Spinner
} from '@chakra-ui/react';
```

## Compound Components

Use Chakra's compound component pattern:

- `Card.Root`, `Card.Body`, `Card.Header`, `Card.Footer`
- `Table.Root`, `Table.Header`, `Table.Body`, `Table.Row`, `Table.Cell`
- `Dialog.Root`, `Dialog.Header`, `Dialog.Body`, `Dialog.Footer`
- `Field.Root`, `Field.Label`, `Field.ErrorText`
- `Alert.Root`, `Alert.Indicator`, `Alert.Content`

## Semantic Tokens

Use semantic color tokens for automatic dark mode:

- Backgrounds: `bg`, `bg.panel`, `bg.subtle`, `bg.muted`
- Text: `fg`, `fg.muted`, `fg.subtle`
- Borders: `border`, `border.muted`

## Color Palettes

Use `colorPalette` prop for consistent theming:

```typescript
<Button colorPalette="blue">Primary</Button>
<Badge colorPalette="green">Success</Badge>
<Alert.Root status="error">Error</Alert.Root>
```

## Layout Components

- `Flex` / `HStack` / `VStack` for flexbox layouts
- `Grid` / `SimpleGrid` for responsive grids
- `Box` for generic containers

```typescript
// Responsive grid
<Grid templateColumns={{ base: '1fr', md: 'repeat(2, 1fr)' }} gap="4">
  {items.map(item => <ItemCard key={item.id} />)}
</Grid>
```

## Form Patterns

```typescript
<Field.Root invalid={!!errors.fieldName}>
  <Field.Label>Label</Field.Label>
  <Input {...register('fieldName')} />
  <Field.ErrorText>{errors.fieldName?.message}</Field.ErrorText>
</Field.Root>
```

## Input Groups

Use `InputGroup` for inputs with icons:

```typescript
<InputGroup
  startElement={
    <Text as="span" className="material-symbols-outlined" fontSize="20px">
      search
    </Text>
  }
>
  <Input placeholder="Search..." />
</InputGroup>
```

## Responsive Patterns

Use responsive props for mobile-first design:

```typescript
<Flex
  flexDirection={{ base: 'column', md: 'row' }}
  alignItems={{ base: 'stretch', md: 'center' }}
  gap={{ base: '2', md: '4' }}
>
```

## Loading States

```typescript
{isLoading && (
  <Flex justify="center" align="center" py="20">
    <VStack gap="4">
      <Spinner size="lg" color="blue.500" />
      <Text color="fg.muted">Loading...</Text>
    </VStack>
  </Flex>
)}
```

